    <!-- Phase 35.2f layer ops (ADR-011 §5 + addendum). Right-side drawer
         exposing add / remove / rename / reorder / visibility / lock per
         §5. `action_layers` is the toolbar trigger contentDescription
         (also reused as the drawer landmark title). `action_add_layer`
         is the drawer FAB; row affordances split: `action_rename_layer`
         labels the inline `OutlinedTextField`, `action_delete_layer`
         labels the row overflow menu's destructive action,
         `action_toggle_layer_visibility` / `action_toggle_layer_lock`
         label the eye + padlock IconButtons, `action_drag_to_reorder`
         labels the Material 3 DragHandle (reorder gesture is long-press-
         and-drag on the handle per §3 of the addendum).
         `label_layer_default_name` is parametric — `AddLayer` dispatches
         from the Screen layer with the next auto-numbered name so the
         ViewModel stays UI-agnostic and locale resolution happens on the
         Compose / SwiftUI side. The initial layer (id `L1`) renders as
         "Layer 1" in EN / "レイヤー 1" in JA.
         `dialog_delete_layer_body` is parametric on cell count and
